---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import SEOHead from '../components/SEOHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';

const title = 'About — Urvash Chheda';
const description = 'Product person. AI builder. Systems thinker.';
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description} currentPage="about">
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <SEOHead title={title} description={description} />
  </Fragment>

  <main class="page-about">

    <!-- ── PAGE HEADER ──────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <header class="about-header">
      <div class="page-label"><span class="s-bracket">[</span>about<span class="s-bracket">]</span></div>
      <h1 class="about-headline">Who I am.</h1>
      <p class="about-sub">Product person. AI builder. Systems thinker. Occasional overengineer.</p>
    </header>

    <!-- ── [01] WHO I AM ────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="section-label">
        <span class="s-bracket">[</span>01<span class="s-bracket">]</span> · WHO I AM
      </div>
      <div class="bio-cols">
        <div class="bio">
          <p class="bio-p">I've spent 8 years at companies where the data infrastructure was always slightly behind what the product needed it to be. That specific tension — product ambition outpacing its own foundation — is the problem I keep getting hired to solve. At this point I think I just find it interesting.</p>
          <p class="bio-p">My technical depth is real but specific. I can read a dbt model, trace a dependency graph, write SQL well enough to validate a data model from the query layer, review an API contract and spot where it'll break at scale. What I do with that is make the technical conversation faster and the decisions cheaper — without anyone needing to translate in the room.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bio-aside">
          <p class="bio-p">I've been a Manchester United fan for over 20 years. This wasn't always a character flaw.</p>
          <p class="bio-p">Eight years in, I've graduated from learning what a data pipeline is to deciding whether one gets built. I'm told this counts as growth. Off the clock: cooking, hiking, sci-fi, and apparently still building software, because I genuinely cannot stop.</p>
          <p class="bio-p">The Office is my most-watched show. I quote it in meetings. Not as a joke. Just as communication.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── [02] HOW I WORK ───────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="section-label">
        <span class="s-bracket">[</span>02<span class="s-bracket">]</span> · HOW I WORK
      </div>
      <div class="items-grid">
        <div class="work-item">
          <div class="item-label">[start with why]</div>
          <p class="item-desc">Before writing a spec, I map the problem. What are users actually doing? What's the system incentive? What breaks if this is wrong?</p>
        </div>
        <div class="work-item">
          <div class="item-label">[prototype to think]</div>
          <p class="item-desc">I use code and data to think. A quick SQL query or a rough Retool dashboard often clarifies requirements faster than a week of meetings.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="work-item">
          <div class="item-label">[write to decide]</div>
          <p class="item-desc">If I can't explain a decision in writing, I haven't made it yet. I write to sharpen thinking, not to document after the fact.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="work-item">
          <div class="item-label">[ship and learn]</div>
          <p class="item-desc">Perfect is the enemy of shipped. I bias toward getting something real in front of users, measuring it, and iterating — not waiting for certainty.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── [03] WHAT I BUILD ─────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="section-label">
        <span class="s-bracket">[</span>03<span class="s-bracket">]</span> · WHAT I BUILD
      </div>
      <div class="items-grid">
        <div class="work-item">
          <div class="item-label">[ML infrastructure]</div>
          <p class="item-desc">The layer between a trained model and actual product usage. Prediction serving, SageMaker endpoints, backfill pipelines. Making research shippable.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="work-item">
          <div class="item-label">[analytics platforms]</div>
          <p class="item-desc">Things that turn messy event streams into decisions someone can act on. Dashboards that don't lie. Metrics that don't gaslight.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="work-item">
          <div class="item-label">[data pipelines]</div>
          <p class="item-desc">dbt models, BigQuery star schemas, CDC binlog pipelines. If the transformation logic lives in an ad-hoc SQL ticket instead of a dbt model, the spec is incomplete before it's written.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="work-item">
          <div class="item-label">[personal builds]</div>
          <p class="item-desc">FinTrack — personal finance intelligence engine. This website — AI chatbot backed by a live Obsidian vault. The builds that exist because I wanted to understand something by owning it end to end.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── [04] WHERE I COME FROM ────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="section-label">
        <span class="s-bracket">[</span>04<span class="s-bracket">]</span> · WHERE I COME FROM
      </div>
      <div class="h-timeline">
        <div class="h-timeline-track">

          <div class="htl-node htl-edu">
            <div class="htl-dot"></div>
            <div class="htl-body">
              <div class="htl-dates">2012–2016</div>
              <div class="htl-badge">[edu]</div>
              <div class="htl-title">B.Tech Computer Science</div>
              <div class="htl-org">NMIMS Mumbai</div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="htl-node htl-work">
            <div class="htl-dot"></div>
            <div class="htl-body">
              <div class="htl-dates">2016–2018</div>
              <div class="htl-badge">[work]</div>
              <div class="htl-title">Founding PM</div>
              <div class="htl-org">MyCrop Technologies</div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="htl-node htl-edu">
            <div class="htl-dot"></div>
            <div class="htl-body">
              <div class="htl-dates">2018–2019</div>
              <div class="htl-badge">[edu]</div>
              <div class="htl-title">M.S. Information Systems</div>
              <div class="htl-org">UMD Smith School</div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="htl-node htl-work">
            <div class="htl-dot"></div>
            <div class="htl-body">
              <div class="htl-dates">2020–2021</div>
              <div class="htl-badge">[work]</div>
              <div class="htl-title">Associate PM</div>
              <div class="htl-org">Aptean</div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="htl-node htl-work">
            <div class="htl-dot"></div>
            <div class="htl-body">
              <div class="htl-dates">2021–2022</div>
              <div class="htl-badge">[work]</div>
              <div class="htl-title">PM</div>
              <div class="htl-org">GrainBridge → Bushel</div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="htl-node htl-work htl-current">
            <div class="htl-dot"></div>
            <div class="htl-body">
              <div class="htl-dates">2023–present</div>
              <div class="htl-badge">[work]</div>
              <div class="htl-title">Senior PM, Analytics &amp; Data Engineering</div>
              <div class="htl-org">Later</div>
            </div>
          </div>

        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── [05] SIGNAL TRACES ────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="section-label">
        <span class="s-bracket">[</span>05<span class="s-bracket">]</span> · SIGNAL TRACES
      </div>
      <p class="graphs-sub">Live data about how I work — from my GitHub and Obsidian knowledge graph.</p>
      <div class="graphs-row">
        <!-- GitHub heatmap -->
        <div class="graph-panel">
          <div class="graph-label">GITHUB · COMMITS</div>
          <canvas id="github-heatmap" class="graph-canvas" aria-label="GitHub contribution heatmap"></canvas>
        </div>
        <!-- Obsidian vault graph -->
        <div class="graph-panel" id="vault-panel">
          <div class="graph-label">OBSIDIAN · VAULT GRAPH</div>
          <canvas
            id="vault-graph"
            class="graph-canvas graph-canvas--tall"
            aria-label="Obsidian vault graph — structural data only, no content exposed"
            title="vault graph — structural data only, no content exposed"
          ></canvas>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

  </main>

  <Footer />

  <div id="commit-tooltip" style="position:fixed; display:none; background:var(--surface); border:1px solid var(--border); padding:0.4rem 0.75rem; font-family:var(--font-mono); font-size:0.72rem; color:var(--text); pointer-events:none; z-index:1000;"></div>

  <!-- D3 from CDN for vault graph -->
  <script is:inline src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/d3/7.8.5/d3.min.js"></script>

  <script>
    const isDark = () => document.documentElement.getAttribute('data-theme') !== 'light';

    // ── GitHub heatmap ───────────────────────────────────────────────
    const WEEKS = 52, DAYS = 7, GAP = 2, CELL = 10;

    type CellMeta = { date: string; count: number };
    let heatmapMeta: CellMeta[][] = [];
    let currentHeatmapGrid: number[][] = [];

    function countToLevel(n: number): number {
      if (n === 0) return 0;
      if (n <= 2)  return 1;
      if (n <= 5)  return 2;
      if (n <= 10) return 3;
      return 4;
    }

    function cellColor(v: number): string {
      if (isDark()) {
        return (['#1a1a18','#003d1f','#006633','#00994d','#00ff88'] as const)[v] ?? '#1a1a18';
      }
      return (['#dddbd4','#c3e8d0','#7dcfa1','#2da862','#00994d'] as const)[v] ?? '#dddbd4';
    }

    function renderHeatmap(canvas: HTMLCanvasElement, grid: number[][]) {
      currentHeatmapGrid = grid;
      const ctx = canvas.getContext('2d')!;
      ctx.clearRect(0, 0, canvas.width, canvas.height);
      grid.forEach((week, w) =>
        week.forEach((v, d) => {
          ctx.fillStyle = cellColor(v);
          ctx.fillRect(w * (CELL + GAP), d * (CELL + GAP), CELL, CELL);
        })
      );
    }

    function formatDate(iso: string): string {
      if (!iso) return '';
      const [y, m, d] = iso.split('-').map(Number);
      const months = ['Jan','Feb','Mar','Apr','May','Jun','Jul','Aug','Sep','Oct','Nov','Dec'];
      return `${months[m - 1]} ${d}, ${y}`;
    }

    function buildFallbackMeta(): CellMeta[][] {
      const today = new Date();
      const start = new Date(today);
      start.setDate(today.getDate() - WEEKS * 7 + 1);
      start.setDate(start.getDate() - start.getDay());
      return Array.from({ length: WEEKS }, (_, w) =>
        Array.from({ length: DAYS }, (_, d) => {
          const dt = new Date(start);
          dt.setDate(start.getDate() + w * 7 + d);
          return { date: dt.toISOString().split('T')[0], count: 0 };
        })
      );
    }

    function setupHeatmapTooltip(canvas: HTMLCanvasElement) {
      const tooltip = document.getElementById('commit-tooltip') as HTMLDivElement | null;
      if (!tooltip) return;

      canvas.addEventListener('mousemove', (e: MouseEvent) => {
        const rect = canvas.getBoundingClientRect();
        const scaleX = canvas.width / rect.width;
        const scaleY = canvas.height / rect.height;
        const px = (e.clientX - rect.left) * scaleX;
        const py = (e.clientY - rect.top) * scaleY;
        const w = Math.floor(px / (CELL + GAP));
        const d = Math.floor(py / (CELL + GAP));

        if (w >= 0 && w < WEEKS && d >= 0 && d < DAYS) {
          const cell = heatmapMeta[w]?.[d];
          if (cell) {
            const ds = formatDate(cell.date);
            tooltip.textContent = cell.count === 0
              ? `No contributions on ${ds}`
              : cell.count === 1
              ? `1 contribution on ${ds}`
              : `${cell.count} contributions on ${ds}`;
            tooltip.style.display = 'block';
            tooltip.style.left = `${e.clientX + 12}px`;
            tooltip.style.top  = `${e.clientY - 28}px`;
          }
        } else {
          tooltip.style.display = 'none';
        }
      });

      canvas.addEventListener('mouseleave', () => {
        tooltip.style.display = 'none';
      });
    }

    async function initHeatmap() {
      const canvas = document.getElementById('github-heatmap') as HTMLCanvasElement;
      if (!canvas) return;
      canvas.width  = WEEKS * (CELL + GAP);
      canvas.height = DAYS  * (CELL + GAP);

      const fallback = Array.from({ length: WEEKS }, () => Array(DAYS).fill(0));
      renderHeatmap(canvas, fallback);
      heatmapMeta = buildFallbackMeta();

      try {
        const res = await fetch('/api/github-activity');
        if (!res.ok) throw new Error('non-200');
        const { weeks } = await res.json() as {
          weeks: { contributionDays: { contributionCount: number; date: string }[] }[]
        };

        const sliced = weeks.slice(0, WEEKS);
        const grid = sliced.map(week =>
          week.contributionDays.slice(0, DAYS).map(day => countToLevel(day.contributionCount))
        );
        heatmapMeta = sliced.map(week =>
          week.contributionDays.slice(0, DAYS).map(day => ({
            date: day.date,
            count: day.contributionCount,
          }))
        );

        while (grid.length < WEEKS) { grid.push(Array(DAYS).fill(0)); heatmapMeta.push(Array(DAYS).fill({ date: '', count: 0 })); }

        renderHeatmap(canvas, grid);
      } catch {
        // fallback already rendered
      }

      setupHeatmapTooltip(canvas);
    }

    // ── Vault graph ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
    type VaultNode = { id: number; folder: string; degree: number; x?: number; y?: number; vx?: number; vy?: number };
    type VaultLink = { source: number | VaultNode; target: number | VaultNode };

    let vaultNodes: VaultNode[] = [];
    let vaultLinks: VaultLink[] = [];

    function nodeColor(folder: string): string {
      const dark = isDark();
      const map: Record<string, [string, string]> = {
        '01-projects':   ['#00ff88', '#00994d'],
        '02-decisions':  ['#4488ff', '#2266cc'],
        '03-learnings':  ['#ff8844', '#cc5522'],
        '04-interviews': ['#888880', '#5a5a54'],
      };
      const pair = map[folder];
      if (pair) return dark ? pair[0] : pair[1];
      return dark ? '#888880' : '#5a5a54';
    }

    function drawGraph(canvas: HTMLCanvasElement, nodes: VaultNode[], links: VaultLink[]) {
      const W = canvas.width, H = canvas.height;
      const ctx = canvas.getContext('2d')!;
      ctx.clearRect(0, 0, W, H);

      const linkColor = isDark() ? 'rgba(255,255,255,0.10)' : 'rgba(0,0,0,0.12)';
      links.forEach(l => {
        const src = typeof l.source === 'object' ? l.source as VaultNode : nodes.find(n => n.id === l.source);
        const tgt = typeof l.target === 'object' ? l.target as VaultNode : nodes.find(n => n.id === l.target);
        if (!src || !tgt || src === tgt) return;
        ctx.beginPath();
        ctx.moveTo(src.x!, src.y!);
        ctx.lineTo(tgt.x!, tgt.y!);
        ctx.strokeStyle = linkColor;
        ctx.lineWidth = 1;
        ctx.stroke();
      });

      nodes.forEach(n => {
        const r = Math.sqrt(n.degree) * 2 + 2;
        ctx.beginPath();
        ctx.arc(n.x!, n.y!, r, 0, Math.PI * 2);
        ctx.fillStyle = nodeColor(n.folder);
        ctx.fill();
      });
    }

    function placeholderGraph() {
      const folders = ['01-projects','02-decisions','03-learnings','04-interviews'];
      const nodes = Array.from({ length: 12 }, (_, i) => ({
        id: i, folder: folders[i % 4], degree: Math.floor(Math.random() * 5) + 1,
      }));
      const links: { source: number; target: number }[] = [];
      while (links.length < 16) {
        const s = Math.floor(Math.random() * 12);
        let t = Math.floor(Math.random() * 11);
        if (t >= s) t++;
        if (!links.some(l => (l.source === s && l.target === t) || (l.source === t && l.target === s))) {
          links.push({ source: s, target: t });
        }
      }
      return { nodes, links };
    }

    async function initVaultGraph() {
      const canvas = document.getElementById('vault-graph') as HTMLCanvasElement;
      if (!canvas || typeof (window as any).d3 === 'undefined') return;

      const bcrect = canvas.getBoundingClientRect();
      canvas.width  = Math.round(bcrect.width)  || 400;
      canvas.height = Math.round(bcrect.height) || 300;

      const W = canvas.width, H = canvas.height;
      const d3 = (window as any).d3;

      let rawNodes: VaultNode[], rawLinks: { source: number; target: number }[];
      try {
        const res = await fetch('/api/vault-graph');
        if (!res.ok) throw new Error('non-200');
        ({ nodes: rawNodes, links: rawLinks } = await res.json());
        if (!rawNodes?.length) throw new Error('empty');
      } catch {
        ({ nodes: rawNodes, links: rawLinks } = placeholderGraph() as any);
      }

      // Deep-copy so D3 mutations don't affect callers; layout runs once, re-draws just repaint
      const simNodes: VaultNode[] = rawNodes.map(n => ({ ...n }));
      const simLinks: VaultLink[] = rawLinks.map(l => ({ ...l }));

      d3.forceSimulation(simNodes)
        .force('charge', d3.forceManyBody().strength(-80))
        .force('link',   d3.forceLink(simLinks).id((d: any) => d.id).distance(55).strength(0.6))
        .force('center', d3.forceCenter(W / 2, H / 2))
        .force('collide', d3.forceCollide(10))
        .alphaDecay(0.025)
        .stop()
        .tick(500);

      simNodes.forEach((n: any) => {
        n.x = Math.max(12, Math.min(W - 12, n.x ?? W / 2));
        n.y = Math.max(12, Math.min(H - 12, n.y ?? H / 2));
      });

      vaultNodes = simNodes;
      vaultLinks = simLinks;

      drawGraph(canvas, vaultNodes, vaultLinks);
    }

    // Re-paint both canvases immediately on theme toggle — no re-layout needed
    new MutationObserver(() => {
      const hc = document.getElementById('github-heatmap') as HTMLCanvasElement | null;
      if (hc && currentHeatmapGrid.length) renderHeatmap(hc, currentHeatmapGrid);

      const vc = document.getElementById('vault-graph') as HTMLCanvasElement | null;
      if (vc && vaultNodes.length) drawGraph(vc, vaultNodes, vaultLinks);
    }).observe(document.documentElement, { attributeFilter: ['data-theme'] });

    window.addEventListener('load', () => {
      initHeatmap();
      initVaultGraph();
    });
  </script>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* ── Page wrapper ─────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .page-about { position: relative; z-index: 1; }

  .section {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    padding: var(--section-gap) var(--pad-r) var(--section-gap) var(--pad-l);
  }

  .s-bracket { color: var(--text-dimmer); }

  /* ── Header ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .about-header {
    padding: 9rem var(--pad-r) 3.5rem var(--pad-l);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .page-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .about-headline {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: clamp(2.2rem, 3vw, 3rem);
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--text);
    line-height: 1.1;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .about-sub {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  /* ── Bio ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .bio-cols {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 0 3rem;
  }

  .bio-cols .bio { max-width: none; }

  .bio-p {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    line-height: 1.9;
    margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
  }
  .bio-p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }

  /* ── How I work / What I build items ─────────────────────────────── */
  .items-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 0 3rem;
  }

  .work-item { margin-bottom: 2rem; }

  .item-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
  }

  .item-desc {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* ── Horizontal timeline ─────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .h-timeline {
    overflow-x: auto;
    -webkit-overflow-scrolling: touch;
    scrollbar-width: thin;
    scrollbar-color: var(--border) transparent;
  }

  .h-timeline-track {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    position: relative;
    padding-top: 1.75rem;
    padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
    min-width: max-content;
  }

  .h-timeline-track::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    top: calc(1.75rem + 6px);
    left: 0;
    right: 0;
    height: 1px;
    background: var(--border);
  }

  .htl-node {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    width: 190px;
    padding: 0 1.5rem;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .htl-dot {
    width: 12px;
    height: 12px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .htl-work .htl-dot {
    background: var(--accent);
    box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px var(--bg), 0 0 0 4px var(--accent);
  }

  .htl-edu .htl-dot {
    background: var(--bg);
    border: 1.5px solid var(--text-dim);
    box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px var(--bg), 0 0 0 4px var(--text-dim);
  }

  .htl-body { width: 100%; }

  .htl-dates {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.68rem;
    color: var(--text-dimmer);
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    margin-bottom: 0.35rem;
  }

  .htl-badge {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.65rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    margin-bottom: 0.45rem;
  }

  .htl-work .htl-badge { color: var(--accent); }
  .htl-edu  .htl-badge { color: var(--text-dim); }

  .htl-title {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--text);
    line-height: 1.4;
    margin-bottom: 0.3rem;
  }

  .htl-org {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--text-dim);
  }

  /* ── Graphs ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .graphs-sub {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .graphs-row {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 1px;
    background: var(--border);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .graph-panel {
    background: var(--surface);
    padding: 1.75rem;
  }

  .graph-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.68rem;
